  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-02-09",
    "date": "2022-03-10T15:09:20Z",
    "text": "Asylum Seeker Work Authorization Act of 2022 \n\nThis bill directs the Department of Homeland Security to provide employment authorization for eligible asylum applicants. Currently, such individuals are not entitled to employment authorization but may be granted such by the Department of Justice.\n\nSuch employment authorization must last for at least two years and be renewable for two-year terms during the period necessary to adjudicate the applicant's asylum claim.\n\nThe bill also shortens the waiting period for receiving employment authorization to 30 days from the filing of the asylum application."
  },
